---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import StoryStep from '../StoryStep.astro';
import Canvas from '../Canvas.astro';
import Item from '../Item.astro';
import zeroMilePost from '../../assets/terminus/zeromilepost.png';
import actualPost from '../../assets/terminus/actualpost.png';
import earlyAtlanta from '../../assets/terminus/earlyatlanta.png';
---

<StoryStep title="Terminus" mediaFirst>
	<!-- Free-flow pocket: drag/resize/rotate these with ?edit. -->
	<Canvas slot="media" fill fitScale class="cluster">
		<!-- DOM order = back → front: earlyAtlanta (back), actualPost, zeroMilePost (front) -->
		<Item
			left="10.4%"
			top="1.4%"
			width="82%"
			phone={{ left: '-0.5%', top: '6%', width: '102.3%', rotate: -1.1 }}
		>
			<Image src={earlyAtlanta} alt="Early Atlanta" />
		</Item>
		<Item
			left="10.5%"
			top="30.6%"
			width="14.4%"
			rotate={-9.2}
			phone={{ left: '65.3%', top: '7.7%', width: '30.1%', rotate: 7.1 }}
		>
			<Image src={actualPost} alt="The actual Zero Mile Post marker" />
		</Item>
		<Item
			left="38.3%"
			top="25.7%"
			width="55.4%"
			rotate={8.2}
			phone={{ left: '-0.2%', top: '35.8%', width: '72.5%', rotate: -9.1 }}
		>
			<Image src={zeroMilePost} alt="The Zero Mile Post" />
		</Item>
	</Canvas>

	<div class="copy">
		<p>
			On the land just cleared of its people, white settlers set out to 	
			something new. It had no harbor, no river port, no natural reason to
			be there—only the spot where a railroad line ended.
		</p>
		<p>
			In 1837, surveyors drove a stake into the ground and called it Terminus, then Marthasville, then Atlanta.
		</p>
	</div>
</StoryStep>

<style>
	/* breathing room below the body text, before the prev/next bar
	   (matches the Peachtree slide) */
	.copy {
		padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}
</style>
